# AI Workflow

- Use `docs/AI_WORKFLOW.md` as the command reference for AI workflow steps.
- Use role-separated templates from `prompts/` when the user invokes a workflow step.
- Prefer `npm run ai:feature` for a new feature and `npm run ai:arch` when only design is needed.
- Treat architecture approval as a human gate. Do not move from `ai:arch` to `ai:impl` until the user approves the plan.
- Keep implementation diffs small and scoped to the approved feature.
- Explain assumptions after changes.
- Log meaningful AI-assisted work in `docs/AI_NOTES.md`.
- Do not duplicate prompt text in rules. Rules point to `prompts/` and `docs/AI_WORKFLOW.md`.
